Wash and dry produce.

Halve @grape tomatoes{4%oz} lengthwise. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating
whites from greens. Core, deseed, and dice @long green pepper{1}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @sour cream{3%tbsp}, @Southwest spice blend{1%tsp}
(2 tsp for 4 servings), @salt{} and @pepper{}. Add @water{} 1 tsp at a time
until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency.

In a separate small bowl, combine tomatoes, scallion whites, and @green salsa{1%tbsp}
(you'll use the rest later). Season with salt and pepper.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat.
Add green pepper and season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring, until softened,
~{4-6%minutes}.

Add @ground beef{10%oz} and another drizzle of oil to same pan. Season with salt,
pepper, and remaining @Southwest spice blend{2%tsp}. Cook, breaking up meat
into pieces, until beef is browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

> If there's excess grease in your pan, carefully pour it out.

Add remaining @green salsa{6%oz} to pan with beef; bring to a simmer over
medium-high heat. Cook until slightly thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in @butter{1%tbsp} until melted. Season with salt and pepper. Turn off heat.

Wrap @flour tortillas{6} in damp #paper towels{} and microwave until warm and
pliable, ~{30%seconds}.

Divide tortillas between plates and fill with beef mixture, @Monterey Jack cheese{1/4%cup},
tomato salsa, and crema. Sprinkle with scallion greens and serve.

> Ground Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.